                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; four group of lines in the incipit
                           page of the text, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each
                           section of the text, alternating with black lines; names of Hebrew
                           letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 23vb, 25ra); elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some other words, e.g., halle luya
                           (e.g., fols. 3vb, 4ra), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols. 7ra, 20ra), ṣällǝyu (e.g.,
                           fols. 7ra, 74ra), ʾǝgäle (e.g., 20ra, 24vb), wa-tǝbl (e.g., fols. 25rb,
                           26va), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g., fols. 25rb, 26ra).</seg>
                     </handNote>
